Nurse Ratchet!  Gald to hear from you! It has been a while.<br><br>
You know, it is interesting that you should take note of my comments. I formulated these thoughts over some time, beginning with a post I made many months ago somewhere here about the corruption and bloated contractors in Nam which I observed first hand. I then made a connection with another post where I remarked that the slow disengagement by Nixon seemed to be motivated by financial situations with the very same contractors. Too much money was being made too fast to have a clean sharp break.<br><br>
Down on post 77, I commented recently on someone's request for feelings about the renewed diplomatic relations with Vietnam. My bottom line was RUBBISH! Then the fellow above from Bechtel with his &quot;PR psychobabble you wanna believe me&quot; statement about what we have now in Vietnam is that &quot;democracy&quot; we always wanted, AND IT ALL CAME TOGETHER. IT REALLY MADE ME SICK...and sick at heart.<br><br>
I must go slowly here, because there are many layers to the onion that I must peel. Then again, it is a metaphysical onion with infinite layers. One thing I feel for certain is that there really is something very, very wrong here.<br><br>
Don't be too hasty with the diploma yet! Read what I posted on post 2, the Wall, and get a feeling for some of the other layers of my metaphysical onion. I feel though, like an eye slowly opening on things, strange things, new things, and just things.<br><br>
Be patient with me, and I will listen, and though I may not always agree, I will give you a fair shake.<br><br>
It is good to hear from you. Don't be a stranger!<br><br>
...Art
